[node name="Terminal" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]TERMINAL COMMANDS[/color][/b]
The terminal is your primary tool for network-level response.

[b]Commands:[/b]
• [color=yellow]help[/color] - Lists all available commands.
• [color=yellow]scan [hostname][/color] - Performs a security scan on the target host. Required to confirm infection before isolation.
• [color=yellow]trace [ip_address][/color] - Traces a suspicious IP to its origin host within the network.
• [color=yellow]isolate [hostname][/color] - Disconnects the target host from the corporate network. Use this to contain active malware or exfiltration.
• [color=yellow]status[/color] - Displays the current terminal status and active isolated hosts.

[b]Note:[/b] Incorrect use of 'isolate' on critical infrastructure (like Servers) may trigger service outages and lead to a [color=red]Terminal Lockout[/color]."
metadata/_tab_index = 0

[node name="Network" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
visible = false
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]NETWORK TOPOLOGY MAP[/color][/b]
Visualizes the physical and logical state of all corporate assets.

[b]Node Status Indicators:[/b]
• [color=cyan]Cyan[/color] - Status: CLEAN. Host is operating within nominal parameters.
• [color=red]Red[/color] - Status: INFECTED. Critical malware detected. Immediate isolation required.
• [color=orange]Orange[/color] - Status: SUSPICIOUS. Anomalous activity detected.
• [color=gray]Gray[/color] - Status: ISOLATED. Host disconnected from network.

[b]Interactivity:[/b]
Right-click any node to access the [b]Context Menu[/b]. This allows you to trigger Scans, Isolation, or Traces directly without typing commands."
metadata/_tab_index = 1

[node name="SIEM" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
visible = false
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]SIEM LOG VIEWER[/color][/b]
The SIEM (Security Information and Event Management) aggregates logs from across the organization.

[b]Usage:[/b]
• [b]Investigation:[/b] Click on a log entry to view detailed metadata (IPs, Hostnames, Messages).
• [b]Evidence:[/b] To solve a ticket with 'Compliant' status, you must attach the required logs as evidence.
• [b]How to Attach:[/b] Select a log, choose the relevant ticket from the dropdown, and click [b]Attach Evidence[/b].

[b]Filtering:[/b]
Use the filter buttons (Security, High Severity) to narrow down thousands of entries to find the 'smoking gun' for your incident."
metadata/_tab_index = 2

[node name="Email" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
visible = false
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]EMAIL ANALYZER[/color][/b]
Most breaches start with a single email. Analyze carefully before acting.

[b]Key Indicators:[/b]
• [b]Spoofing:[/b] Check if the 'From' address matches the expected internal domain.
• [b]Malicious Links:[/b] Hover over or scan links to check for suspicious domains or phishing redirects.
• [b]Attachments:[/b] Scan all attachments for malware signatures.

[b]Actions:[/b]
• [color=red]Quarantine[/color]: Use when you are certain the email is malicious.
• [color=green]Approve[/color]: Use for legitimate business communication.

[i]Warning: Misidentifying a legitimate executive email as phishing will cause reputation loss.[/i]"
metadata/_tab_index = 3

[node name="Procedures" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
visible = false
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]INCIDENT RESPONSE PROCEDURES[/color][/b]

[b]Resolution Strategies:[/b]
• [b]Compliant:[/b] The standard operating procedure. Requires all evidence (logs) to be attached. No risk of missing hidden consequences.
• [b]Efficient:[/b] Priority is speed. No evidence required, but high risk of missing 'Hidden Risks' that cause later breaches.
• [b]Emergency:[/b] Immediate resolution for catastrophic events. Use only when time is critical.

[b]Special Recovery Tools:[/b]
• [b]Decryption Utility:[/b] Used after ransomware containment to restore encrypted assets. Requires active pattern matching.
• [b]IP Traceroute:[/b] Used during data exfiltration incidents to reveal the true origin host behind a suspicious IP.

[b]Analyst Archetypes:[/b]
Your performance determines your reputation:
• [b]By-the-Book:[/b] High compliance, slow but safe.
• [b]Cowboy:[/b] High efficiency, fast but dangerous.
• [b]Negligent:[/b] Letting alerts time out."
metadata/_tab_index = 4

[node name="Examples" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
visible = false
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]WALKTHROUGH: RESOLVING AN INCIDENT[/color][/b]

[b]Example Ticket:[/b] [i]Scheduled System Maintenance[/i]
[b]Goal:[/b] Verify that the backup service finished successfully.

[b]Step 1: Investigation[/b]
Open the [color=yellow]SIEM Log Viewer[/color]. You are looking for a \"Success\" message. 
[i]Hint: Look for Source: \"System\" and Severity: \"Info\".[/i]

[b]Step 2: Attaching Evidence[/b]
1. Click the log: [color=green]\"Scheduled backup completed successfully\"[/color].
2. At the bottom, click the dropdown and select the maintenance ticket.
3. Click [b]Attach[/b].

[b]Step 3: Closing the Loop[/b]
1. Open the [color=yellow]Ticket Queue[/color].
2. Select the ticket. You will see [color=green]Evidence: 1/1[/color].
3. Click [b]Resolve Incident[/b].
4. Choose [b]Compliant Resolution[/b].

[b][color=orange]WHY COMPLIANT?[/color][/b]
If you skip Step 2 and choose [b]Efficient[/b], you close the ticket faster but risk missing \"Hidden Risks.\" For example, if a malware beacon was hidden in those logs and you didn't check them, the attack will [color=red]Escalate[/color] later in your shift!"
metadata/_tab_index = 5

[node name="Incidents" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
visible = false
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]INCIDENT CATALOG & PROCEDURES[/color][/b]

[b]1. PHISH-001: Phishing Campaign Alert[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] SIEM / Email
• [b]Steps:[/b] Check SIEM alerts, review email headers, verify clicks.

[b]2. SPEAR-PHISH-001: Spear Phishing Investigation[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] Email
• [b]Steps:[/b] Inspect headers for spoofing, scan attachments, check domain reputation.

[b]3. MALWARE-CONTAIN-001: Malware Containment[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] Terminal / Network Map
• [b]Steps:[/b] Scan host WORKSTATION-45, isolate host if infected, verify isolation.

[b]4. RANSOM-001: Ransomware Alert[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] Network Map / Decryption Utility
• [b]Steps:[/b] Isolate target server, initiate decryption puzzle, verify recovery.

[b]5. SOCIAL-001: Social Engineering Attempt[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] Email / SIEM
• [b]Steps:[/b] Check call logs, draft security alert, update security awareness.

[b]6. INSIDER-001: Suspicious Data Access[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] SIEM
• [b]Steps:[/b] Search Jane Doe logs, identify unusual file access, report to Senior Analyst.

[b]7. DATA-EXFIL-001: Data Exfiltration Alert[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] Terminal (Trace) / SIEM
• [b]Steps:[/b] Trace suspicious IP to internal host, block connection, verify containment.

[b]8. AUTH-FAIL-GENERIC: Multiple Auth Failures[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] SIEM / Email
• [b]Steps:[/b] Verify jsmith identity, reset password if requested, monitor failures.

[b]9. SYS-MAINT-GENERIC: Scheduled Maintenance[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] SIEM
• [b]Steps:[/b] Monitor patch logs, verify 'smbd' service, confirm connectivity.

[b]10. BLACK-TICKET-REDEMPTION: Forensic Post-Mortem[/b]
• [b]Tool:[/b] SIEM / Email / Terminal
• [b]Steps:[/b] Identify delivery vector, trace lateral movement, verify recovery."
metadata/_tab_index = 6
